OL,3,CChannel Islands to tax large companies
OL,4,Cmore under global initiative
OL,6,FDeputy Ian Gorst, Jersey's Assistant
OL,7,FTreasury Minister, told ITV News:
OL,8,F"Those businesses will have to pay the
OL,9,Ftax wherever they are globally and
OL,10,Ftherefore they can't just leave Jersey
OL,11,Fand avoid paying the tax.
OL,13,F"It's really important that we play
OL,14,Four part in the development of this
OL,15,Finternational tax, as we have done,
OL,16,Fand then we implement it here so that
OL,17,FJersey profits are taxed in Jersey."
OL,19,FHe added this tax would only apply to
OL,20,Faround 1,400 companies and that the
OL,21,FGovernment is "not complacent".
