OL,3,CChannel Islands to tax large companies
OL,4,Cmore under global initiative
OL,6,F'Pillar two' was designed to stop
OL,7,Fmultinationals from putting their
OL,8,Fmoney into jurisdictions that offered
OL,9,Fthem a more attractive rate of tax.
OL,11,FWith an increasingly global economy,
OL,12,Fit is designed to tackle what is
OL,13,Fdescribed as 'profit shifting'.
OL,15,FNow of course, the Channel Islands
OL,16,Fhave often sold themselves as places
OL,17,Fwith low taxes.
OL,19,FLocate Jersey, who help the wealthy
OL,20,Fmove to the island, advertises "low
OL,21,Fpersonal and business taxes".
